reviews.review_text: Gotten my prescriptions here for years, they always have whatever I need within 48 hours of me placing my prescription (which is much faster than other places I have been)!
Helpful, efficient and timely...
Dont know what all the hate is about.  I have always had good and friendly service for the 17 years I have been coming here.
not open 24hrs!!

I tried to get my prescription here and they told me it was expired? I had only had it placed there 2 months ago, and was told prescriptions legally have to be on file for 2 years before expiring by my doctor. This isn t my first issue with this pharmacy either, I ll be going somewhere else, many other options out there.

Worst pharmacy service I ve ever received. After sitting there chatting for 20 minutes while I waited in their view, 3 of them, I was finally served by an arrogant condescending man who treated me like I was in the wrong for finally saying excuse me. I could hear what you re talking about, it was not work related, sir. However, my attendance to your location is, do your job! He then proceeded to give me vague answers and sigh repeatedly as I asked the difference between medications so I could choose one to purchase. The judgemental arrogant attitude I received, coupled with the fact he told me I couldn t get my inhaler filled until the next day (it was only 4pm) even tho I told him I was short of breath and it s just ventolin that I ALREADY HAVE A REFILL ON FILE FOR, leads me to give them a 1/10. I have several other negative experiences too this is not a one off. This is a terrible pharmacy who doesn t care about their patients health, just about their profits.

Ive never written a negative review before, but I thought I should warn that Ive had a number of needlessly tense interactions at this pharmacy while simply refilling medications. There are some nice staff as well so I dont want to paint too broad a brush, but multiple staff made the process of just picking up medications a pain -- switching pharmacies now.

The pharmacist Mr Ahmed is the rudest person I have ever met. He isnt patient and with his body language and tone of voice he shows he is not happy with his job. I turned in a complaint letter to the manager and apparently nothing happened. People like Mr Ahmee shouldnt work in customer service. His rude attitude deters people from coming to the pharmacy in the hope not to come across with him.

Exactly   I feel mistreated and disrespected at this pharmacy. They dont have your meds ready or tell my dad he has already picked up his heart meds when he is out of them. This man the manager is a rude guy pretty much told me to my face I was lying. If u dint have too deal with this rude pharmacy I wouldnt choose it. Til they learn compassion and respect.
Absolutely the worst. Always a long wait, perscriptions are NEVER ready when they say, if you do a renewal on the phone they have no record of it when you go to pick it up.

When I asked the doctor to explain how to use the medicine, he (mr ahmad)started talking very rudely and mockingly. Unfortunately, I had a very bad experience with this pharmacy and him. This is not the first time this has happened and they did not know how can use my insurance

This is the worst pharmacy ever. It is not enough that you have to wait for 45 min to pick your medication ( I came 48 hours after my confirmed pickup date) I also have to wait for 30 min on the phone to fill in my prescription cause someone very smart at loblaw decided that the online refill system is too good and customers were using it to save their and the staff time so they decommissioned the system a year ago without putting another one in place. By far the worst

Very disorganized pharmacy and staff who don t care about people s time and scheduling. First, they ve lost my prescription, claiming that my physician didn t send it. Then, I got my physician to resend the prescription, and when they received it, I was told that it would be ready by 5:30 pm the same day. They even claimed it on my insurance which was fully covered. I had to commute back to the pharmacy again. When I visited the pharmacy at 5:45 pm, my prescription wasn t ready and at that moment they started to make it ready and collect the pills. The frustrating part is that they realized that they didn t have it!

I dropped off my prescription on a Friday afternoon. When I went back to pick it up on Tuesday afternoon, it was NOT ready. This was the 3rd time this has happened at this location. I used the auto-fill phone number and my meds were never ready when I arrived on the date given. Avoid!

The last 6 customer that went by here had their meds all delay. Even though all of us received confirmation that it will be done in 5minutes 1 hour later, still not done. Staff seems really short handed, could either use a bit more help or just give more realistic time. So be prepared to make a few trips. Or come in 24 to 48hrs after the confirmed pickup time to save yourself previous time
The new pharmacist has no idea about how to talk to people. He is aggressive without any reason. He needs training. Im moving to another pharmacy. Other employees are great though.

Worst pharmacy EVER. Go literally anywhere else. Problems this bad cant be blamed on lousy attitudes or bad customer service. There must be some major systemic malfunction here keeping employees from having enough product  to prepare the correct medications in the right time.

Incredibly disorganized, dishonest and irresponsible. Prepare to be told to wait hours and also to keep waiting half an hour after that. The load on them is medium at best, but the chaos in the back and the processes there cripple them. Avoid unless you dont have anything better to do. And expect this every time.

omg, horrible experience 2 weeks ago, long line and staff did not care! Only one inexperienced staff dealt with all customers pick up instead of getting another line open to serve. today, I tried to call to confirm my prescribed medication is ready (prescription arrived 2 days ago) and they picked my call and hang up repeatedly. Horrible, no star if I can give

After 3 times booking for an injection. A half an hour heads up to them to make sure this time day can get it done. Arrived on time and Mr. Ahmed Told me oh book for another time we are busy! Once I objected to the situation and became the bad guy, they did the injection. But question is why so much drama? if your busy hire more people to work. If you cant just dont book new clients...all in all not the best expereince.

Im still not sure how they are so bad at being a pharmacy, between losing prescriptions, claiming I need to pay, telling me my doctor prescribed something wrong...  Its not worth the trouble, go elsewhere for your prescriptions.

Edit: ive been trying to get my urgent medication at this pharmacy today and nobody answers the phone. What a horrible experience. The phone is always busy when I try to call this pharmacy. Order the medication in advance and when I get there its not ready. I only pick up here cause its close to my house.

Poor customer service I had to come back again after 1 hour of waiting because my prescription wasnt processed due to someones mistake it wasnt first time happening to me. It was second time Worst pharmacy Ive even been
Theyre always behind! I understand theyre busy but even if you delay the pick up for two days, they still tell you well get it ready in 15 minutes.

1 step above useless. Gestational diabetes blood test strips were  asked for at 3:20. 15 minutes.  Did the shopping returning at about 3:40. 5 minutes. Waited patiently for about another 25 minutes and got in line again. When asked they said, oh, that ones ready and was told the person who was handling the prescription was off. Except that we watched that person the entire time we were waiting as they are the ones that told us 5 minutes. They called 2 other people by name while we were waiting, 7 months pregnant, with a 6 year old. Unlikely to EVER return.

Im pretty sure this is the most incompetent pharmacy on earth, But i have to deal with them because they are the only pharmacy close to me. I have not been able to come here once without them making a big mistake and making it much harder for me to get my athsma medication!

Go elsewhere if you need a pharmacy! There is no way to call them as the number isnt accepting calls, so you cant check if your prescription is ready (which it probably isnt).  The staff arent polite and try and charge even if you have coverage.
Would put 0 star if I could, incredibly rude staff.
So slow and lazy. Previous owner was much better.
Almost every time I try to pick up my prescription it is not ready even if it is the day after it is supposed to be ready. And the pharmacist does not seem to care.

Long wait times, rude staff, basically called me a liar when I faxed in a prescription and came to pick up without bringing the original. They said they told me it was law to bring it in when they left me the ready for pickup voicemail, but thats not true. If they had I would have brought it in. Also, my doctor wrote x3 for refills but they disregarded it and put 0 refills because it wasnt in the form at the top.  I DID get ruder than I should have, but late in the evening, grocery shopping before bed, didnt expect to be treated so badly and have to worry about leaving without my meds. They eventually gave me my prescription but made it clear they thought I was lying. It was a basic prescription for a daily med I need to survive... nothing illicit and certainly not worth them being jerks over. Will be returning to Shoppers Drug mart where they respect their customers, never should have changed.

I was quoted 45 minutes,  2 hours later my prescription wasnt ready.  Everyone waiting in line with me had a similar story. She then told me to wait 5 more minutes,  only to wait another 45 minutes!!!!! Save your time.  Will never go here again
Such misrable pharmacy. Their staff have attitude and their service is so bad. It took my wife almost two hours to get the eye drop!!! I believe they are re-inventing the wheel!!

I came in for a flu shot and the pharmacist Ellen didn t wash her hands or sanitize after touching the door and picking something off the floor. I even asked her to sanitize please but she continued to prepare my flu shot, didn t even prime the needle, and only then put gloves onto her dirty hands to give me the shot.
I have come back to make another review to reiterate how shockingly inefficient this place still is. Nothing more to be said other than go anywhere else.
3 hour wait for a puffer...... can you not just grab it off the shelf and give it to me. What an absolute joke.
Often takes nearly double the time quoted for a prescription and I usually wait over 3 minutes to even be acknowledged when theres nobody else in line and I am clearly seen by multiple pharmacists.

Months ago I went in and they didn t have the drug I needed. Went last week and we were made to wait an obscene amount of time after completing our grocery shop. This site needs a serious upgrade. I don t recommend even if you are desperate!!
They have bad service and no respect for customers
Horrible.. they dont even know what they selling. No responsible people, no honor, low intelligence staffs..If you have to buy something there, you have to threeple check what did you receive there.
2/3 of my prescriptions that I came to pick up today that I dropped off 4 days ago were not ready.
Rude staff and long wait time. I dont recommend this place at all
I have been there twice and the pharmacist is not friendly at all. Wont go there anymore!
Worst customer service I had ever in a pharmacy.
Not stocked!
It is terrible,terrible pharmacy. Their customer care is below zero.
Nothing is ever ready on time
Extremely rude employees, want nothing to do with helping you.
Go somewhere else. Slowest pharmacy I have encountered.
Worst employees ever
this place is shet....
